						               													<description>&amp;#229;&amp;#173;&amp;#164;&amp;#232;&amp;#135;&amp;#163;&amp;#229;&amp;#132;&amp;#146;&amp;#229;&amp;#173;&amp;#144;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#154;&amp;#230;&amp;#152;&amp;#142;&amp;#230;&amp;#156;&amp;#157;&amp;#231;&amp;#154;&amp;#132;&amp;#232;&amp;#166;&amp;#134;&amp;#230;&amp;#187;&amp;#133; (Last Loyalists: The Fall of Ming Dynasty) is a strategic wargame to simulate the Southern Ming dynasty in 17 century in China. It is a fast-paced and card-driven wargame for 2-3 players in 2 to 3 hours. Players commands the Army of Qing Dynasty, Ming Dynasty, and Great Xi and use Strategy cards to maneuver tactics, and build infantry, cavalry, or navy units to conquer areas and win the victory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every player takes a turn by selecting one major action and one roundel action. Roundel action includes politics, march, assembly, and new year actions.  Major actions includes events, farming, strategy, operations, and award actions. Cards and units also represents your resource and you need to use award action to control the loyalty of your neutral generals. Player wins the game by getting 10 points in any round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
